{"_path":"/posts/how-get-tor-24-ubuntu-and-slackware","_dir":"posts","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"How to get Tor 2.4 on Ubuntu and Slackware.","description":"How and why to get the latest and safest version of anonymising software Tor on your Ubuntu or Slackware box.","imagesource":null,"imagecredit":null,"imageFilename":"2013.09.09T060000_how-get-tor-24-ubuntu-and-slackware.png","createdAt":"2013-09-09T06:00:00","updatedAt":"2013-09-09T06:00:00","readingTime":{"text":"1 min read","minutes":0.1,"time":6000,"words":20},"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With all the recent fuss about "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://gizmodo.com/the-nsa-can-crack-almost-any-type-of-encryption-1258954266","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the NSA being able to decrypt pretty much anything they like"}]},{"type":"text","value":", it's more important than ever to focus on ensuring you're running up to date server software. I also came across "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://arstechnica.com/security/2013/09/majority-of-tor-crypto-keys-could-be-broken-by-nsa-researcher-says/","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"an article detailing exactly how out of the loop Tor exit node providers are"}]},{"type":"text","value":". This I find concerning for far too many reasons to list, and hope here to provide some information on how to stay up to date. Version 2.4 of Tor is still in RC phase, but seems to be widely regarded "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://lists.torproject.org/","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"on the mailing lists"}]},{"type":"text","value":" as stable enough for people to adopt officially."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The encryption techniques Tor 2.3 and previous used were RSA-1024/DH-1024 with AES-128. These are some of the most popular cryptographic techniques currently employed, and thus are considered to be some of the most likely to have been broken by the NSA's crypto team. The RC edition uses ECC (Elliptic Curve Cryptography), which is generally considered to be far better - although "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.schneier.com/blog/archives/2013/09/the_nsas_crypto_1.html","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"there are doubts from some experts"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"By far one of the most common Linux base distributions are Debian, and its various derivatives. The Tor Project have taken this into account, and "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.torproject.org/docs/debian","target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"provide .deb packages for many of these"}]},{"type":"text","value":". To ensure you're using version 2.4, you must currently use the development branch - at least until the official release date."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here's a simple set of instructions for getting the latest edition of Tor installed on your server..."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"step-1-add-apt-repository"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Step 1: Add apt repository"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Add the following lines to /etc/apt/sources.list.d/tor, or i that folder doesn't exist, /etc/apt/sources.list"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark","code":"deb     http://deb.torproject.org/torproject.org <distribution> main\ndeb     http://deb.torproject.org/torproject.org experimental-<distribution> main</distribution></distribution>\n","language":"bash","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":"